        "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1\n\nReviewed both files, look good, I`ll give my +1.\nHowever - we can improve. In Honolulu release there was a change in the DCAE Cloudify, in order to make it possible to create Blueprints, which would support set-up of additional services in IPv6 networks. That is a stright-forward change in the Bleuprint.\n\nI think, we could simplify the description by demonstrating there, how to add an additional port in VES collector blueprint, which will be exposed in IPv6 network. This shall be a failry simple blueprint modification (and You`re anyway doing a blueprint modification to utilize X.509 certificates with a Cert Manager/ CMP v2).",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
